    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1985-05-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1985-05-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <head>380. Telegram From the Embassy in Bulgaria to the Department of State<note
                        n="1" type="source" xml:id="d380fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Foreign Policy File, D850372–0084. Confidential; Priority. Sent for
                        information to Ankara, Istanbul, Munich, Rome, and the mission to <gloss
                            target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">1985.</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Sofia</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1985-05-28"
                            >May 28, 1985, 0829Z</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <!--<pb facs="d380-2" n="2" type="facsimile" xml:id="d380-2"/>-->
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>The Antonov <rs corresp="recsNQ59E979BphyM" type="topic">Trial</rs> in
                        Rome: Bulgarian Response.</item>
                </list>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>REF</head>
                    <item>Sofia 1962.<note n="2" xml:id="d380fn2">Telegram 1962 from Sofia, May 23,
                            reported on Bulgarian counter-<rs corresp="recz6YHYRY8K7jQX1"
                                type="topic">propaganda</rs> on the eve of the Antonov <rs
                                corresp="recsNQ59E979BphyM" type="topic">trial</rs>. (Department of
                            State, Central <rs corresp="rectqbCKMJaN5yPfG" type="topic">Foreign
                                Policy</rs> File, D850366–0971)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Confidential—Entire text.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Bulgaria greeted the opening day of the Antonov <rs
                            corresp="recsNQ59E979BphyM" type="topic">trial</rs> in Rome, Monday May
                        27, with <gloss target="#t_BTA_1">BTA</gloss> (Bulgarian press agency)
                        declaration and a flood of articles declaring his innocence.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>We assume FBIS will carry the full text of the <gloss target="#t_BTA_1"
                            >BTA</gloss> declaration<note n="3" xml:id="d380fn3">Not found.</note>
                        which broke no new ground, but did say that world <rs
                            corresp="rec1K4XtTHBIl41Sv" type="topic">public opinion</rs> recognized
                        the “campaign” against Bulgaria and that many publications rejected the
                        “Bulgarian connection”, pointing instead towards the involvement of
                        “intelligence centers of <gloss target="#t_NATO_1">NATO</gloss>.”</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>A report from Rome<note n="4" xml:id="d380fn4">Telegram 13428 from Rome,
                            May 28. (Department of State, Central <rs corresp="rectqbCKMJaN5yPfG"
                                type="topic">Foreign Policy</rs> File, D850372–0717)</note> also
                        noted that the interest of the United States in the <rs
                            corresp="recsNQ59E979BphyM" type="topic">trial</rs> was shown by the
                        presence of four observers from the <gloss target="#t_US_1">US</gloss>
                        Embassy in Rome.</item>
                    <!--<pb facs="d380-3" n="3" type="facsimile" xml:id="d380-3"/>-->
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Local <rs corresp="recxRLdoJs9wm7rck" type="topic">press coverage</rs> of
                        the <rs corresp="recsNQ59E979BphyM" type="topic">trial</rs> May 27 was
                        massive—lengthy <rs corresp="recUkDvsgHuU90wRT" type="topic">radio</rs>
                        commentaries and a special program on prime time <rs
                            corresp="recAsWFxRUa5DhtTM" type="topic">television</rs>.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Lake</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
